Highveld Stereo presenter and club DJ MacGyver Mukwevho survived possible jail time by a whisker after his girlfriend and baby mama withdrew her assault charges this week. The woman, who cannot be identified for legal reasons, had opened a case against the former YFM DJ at the Midrand police station two weeks ago, claiming he had kicked and beat her to a pulp. She withdrew the charges of assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm against him on Wednesday. The young radio maestro, who left YFM under a cloud after making derogatory statements against gay people, spent a night in the police holding cells as a result of the charges. TO READ THE FULL STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD AT YOUR NEAREST STORE